{"title_page": "Spymesat", "text_new": "'''SpyMeSat''' is a mobile application for iOS and Android that computes and visualizes overhead satellite pass predictions for any selected location in real-time from participating commercial and unclassified government high-resolution imaging satellites. SpyMeSat was developed by Orbit Logic, a software company based in [[Greenbelt, Maryland]]. The app debuted in 2013. SpyMeSat also includes the ability to browse and download high-resolution satellite images from various imagery providers, or task imaging satellites to take a new image of any user-defined location.<ref>{{cite web\n |url= https://www.space.com/23225-iphone-app-spy-satellites.html\n |title= New iPhone App Lets You See Which Spy Satellites Are Watching You\n |author= Leonard David\n |date= October 16, 2013\n |website= space.com\n |publisher= Future US, Inc. \n |access-date= April 2, 2020\n |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url= https://technofaq.org/posts/2019/08/why-you-should-buy-satellite-images-from-spymesat/\n |title= Why You Should Buy Satellite Images From SpyMeSat\n |author= Sunit Nandi\n |date= August 26, 2019\n |website= technofaq.org\n |publisher= Techno FAQ\n |access-date= April 2, 2020\n |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Features==\n* Provides real-time imaging satellite overflight notifications for the user's current location or location of choice.\n* Access to purchase \u00e0 la carte high-resolution satellite images from various providers including [[Maxar Technologies]],<ref>{{cite web\n |url= https://www.digitalglobe.com/ecosystem/resellers\n |title= DigitalGlobe certified resellers\n |author= <!--Not stated--> \n |date= \n |website= digitalglobe.com\n |publisher= Maxar\n |access-date= April 2, 2020\n |quote=}}</ref> [[Planet Labs]], and [[KOMPSAT]].\n* Option to download imagery in GeoTIFF format\n* Ability to submit a new tasking request to an Earth-imaging satellite to take a new picture of any location on Earth.<ref>{{cite web\n |url= http://www.si-imaging.com/newsroom/?pageid=1&%3Bmod=document&uid=96&mod=document\n |title= Task KOMPSAT Using SpyMeSat\n |author= <!--Not stated--> \n |date= December 26, 2016\n |website= si-imaging.co\n |publisher= SI Imaging Services Co., Ltd\n |access-date= April 2, 2020\n |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url= https://spacenews.com/spymesat-app-developer-looking-to-contract-more-satellites/\n |title= SpyMeSat App Developer Looking To Contract More Satellites\n |author= Jonathan Charlton\n |date= June 25, 2015\n |website= spacenews.com\n |publisher= Space News\n |access-date= April 2, 2020\n |quote=}}</ref>\n\nFeatures of the SpyMeSat mobile app are protected by U.S. Patents 9344994<ref>{{cite patent\n| country = US\n| number = 9344994\n| status = Active\n| title = Method for providing imaging satellite opportunity notifications on a mobile device\n| pubdate = 2015-09-10\n| gdate\t= 2016-05-17\n| fdate\t= 2015-02-25\n| pridate = \n| invent1 = Alexander Herz\n| assign1 = Orbit Logic, Inc.\n| assign2 = \n| class\t= \n| url = http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&Sect2=HITOFF&p=1&u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&r=2&f=G&l=50&co1=AND&d=PTXT&s1=9344994&OS=9344994&RS=9344994\n}}</ref> and 9779301.<ref>{{cite patent\n| country = US\n| number = 9779301\n| status = Active\n| title = Method for providing imaging satellite opportunity notifications on a mobile device\n| pubdate = 2016-08-11\n| gdate\t= 2017-10-03\n| fdate\t= 2016-04-15\n| pridate = \n| invent1 = Alexander Herz\n| assign1 = Orbit Logic, Inc.\n| assign2 = \n| class\t= \n| url = http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO2&Sect2=HITOFF&p=1&u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsearch-bool.html&r=1&f=G&l=50&co1=AND&d=PTXT&s1=9344994&OS=9344994&RS=9344994\n}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n*2017 [[United States Geospatial Intelligence Foundation]] Industry Achievement Award <ref>{{cite web\n |url= https://usgif.org/news/878-usgif-presents-2017-achievement-awards\n |title= USGIF Presents 2017 Achievement Awards\n |author= <!--