hard The Troll ([[Capilano_(electoral_district)|Capilano]]) 688 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Lesosky, Louis Crowbird ([[Cowichan\u2014Malahat\u2014The_Islands|Cowichan-Malhat-The Islands]]) 444 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Maddocks, Bob ([[Esquimalt\u2014Saanich|Esquimalt-Saanich]]) 548 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n===Storey, Kyle ([[Kamloops-Shuswap]]) 237 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Coffey, Frank Tee Pee Red ([[Nanaimo-Alberni]]) 591 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Kruger, Andre The Rock ([[Okanagan-Similkameen]]) 317 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n===Courchene, Albert The Cad ([[Surrey\u2014White_Rock\u2014North_Delta|Surrey-White Rock-North Delta]]) 440 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Longworth, David J. ([[Vancouver Centre]]) 337 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Lyttle, Dandy Randy ([[Vancouver East]]) 198 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===McDonald, Verne John Eh ([[Vancouver Quadra]]) 405 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Fleming, Linda ([[Vancouver South]]) 327 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Higgins, Rhino Kirk ([[Victoria_(electoral_district)|Victoria]]) 446 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n==[[Manitoba]]==\nManitoban Rhino candidates were generally uncontested for fourth.\n===Campbell, Roland ([[Churchill\u2014Keewatinook_Aski|[formerly] Churchill]]) 352 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Feilburg, Lawrence ([[Provencher]]) 433 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Bergen, Honest Don ([[Winnipeg\u2014Birds_Hill|Winnipeg-Birds Hill]]) 322 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Balderstone, Smilin Dave ([[Winnipeg\u2014Fort_Garry|Winnipeg-Fort Garry]]) 405 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n==[[New Brunswick]]==\n===Boucher, Amede Le Terrible ([[Acadie\u2014Bathurst| [formerly] Gloucester]]) 362 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n===Boudreau, Jules Cesar ([[Acadie\u2014Bathurst|[formerly] Gloucester]]) 736 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nBoth candidates combined and Boudreau himself ranked 4th.\n===Doucet, Arthur ([[Restigouche_(electoral_district)|Restigouche]]) 692 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n==[[Nova Scotia]]==\n===Moors, Mark ([[Kings\u2014Hants|[formerly] Annapolis Valley-Hants]]) 343 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Tudor, Martha ([[South_Shore\u2014St._Margarets|[formerly] South Shore]]) 433 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n==[[Ontario]]==\n===Reid, David J. ([[Beaches_(electoral_district)|Beaches]]) 214 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Butterfield, Vicki ([[Toronto\u2014Danforth|[formerly] Broadview\u2014Greenwood]])===\nButterfield, wife of noted computer expert [[Jim Butterfield]],<ref name=\"hooktorpet\" /> ran a low-profile campaign.  The Rhinoceros Party announced that she was \"following the lead of another, more prominent candidate, and is hiding from the public\".<ref name=\"vicki\" />  This was likely a reference to [[Liberal Party of Canada|Liberal]] leader [[Pierre Trudeau]].  She received 196 votes (0.61%), finishing fourth against [[New Democratic Party of Canada|New Democratic Party]] incumbent [[Bob Rae]].\n\n===Thorning, Steve ([[Guelph (electoral district)|Guelph]]) 272 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Sabzali, James E. S. ([[Hamilton_West_(Canadian_electoral_district)|Hamilton West]]) 304 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Sharp, Edward T. ([[Kingston and the Islands]]) 373 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Wright, Douglas ([[Kitchener_(electoral_district)|Kitchener]]) 292 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Showers, Stewart ([[London West]]) 224 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Cockerell, Alan ([[Nepean-Carleton]]) 658 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Stranart, J. C. ([[Ontario_(electoral_district)|Ontario]]) 313 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Langille, David ([[Ottawa Centre]]) 358 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Ashby, Graham Prickes ([[Ottawa-Vanier]]) 519 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Elson, Mark ([[Peterborough\u2014Kawartha|[formerly] Peterborough]]) 243 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Yates, Geoff ([[Toronto_Centre|[formerly] Rosedale]]) 319 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Douglas, John ([[Spadina_(electoral_district)|Spadina]]) 250 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Pileggi, Salvatore ([[Spadina_(electoral_district)|Spadina]]) 146 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Lake, Fred Horny ([[St._Catharines_(electoral_district)|St. Catharines]]) 230 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Armour, Liza ([[Toronto\u2014St._Paul%27s|St. Paul's]]) 311 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Lalonde, Raymond ([[Sudbury_(electoral_district)||Sudbury]]) 288 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Nigol, Rick ([[Waterloo_(electoral_district)|Waterloo]]) 330 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Matheson, John ([[York East]]) 237 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Oliver, Mark ([[York-Peel]]) 589 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n==[[Qu\u00e9bec]]==\n===Lambert, Germain ([[Beauce (electoral district)|Beauce]]) 624 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th, beat the [[New Democratic Party|NDP]] (404 votes)\n===Chabot, Andree ([[Bellechasse (electoral district)|Bellechasse]]) 815 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th, beat the [[New Democratic Party|NDP]] (730 votes)\n===Des Gagne, Ti-Pit Claude ([[Berthier\u2014Maskinong\u00e9|Berthier\u2014Maskinong\u00e9]]) 728 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 3rd behind the Liberals and the Progressive Conservatives. NDP did not run a candidate.\n\n===Grenier, Philippe Sarto ([[Blainville\u2014Deux-Montagnes|Blainville-Deux Montagnes]]) 1,685 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Leblanc, Louis Philippe Tulipe ([[Bonaventure_(electoral_district)|Bonaventure-Iles-De-La-Madeleine]]) 917 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Michaud, Helene ([[Chambly (electoral district)|Chambly]]) 1,724 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Bernard, Denis Van ([[Charlesbourg\u2014Haute-Saint-Charles|[formerly] Charlesbourg]]) 3,066 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===[[Guy Lalibert\u00e9|Lalibert\u00e9, Guy Pantouffe]] ([[Charlevoix_(electoral_district)|Charlevoix]]) 945 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n[[Guy Lalibert\u00e9]] Later went on to found [[Cirque de Soleil]]\n\n===Vaillancourt, Pierre Elliot ([[Alfred-Pellan|Duvernay]]) 2,479 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Antonyszyn, Polack Eugene ([[Gamelin (electoral district)|Gamelin]]) 1,640 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Mainville, Francis Vitesse ([[Gasp\u00e9 (electoral district)|Gaspe]]) 759 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n===Penzes, Francois R. ([[Gatineau]]) 640 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n===Gougeon, Diane ([[Hochelaga\u2014Maisonneuve|Hochelaga-Maisonneuve]]) 1,412 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Dompierre, Sylvain ([[Hull\u2014Aylmer|[formerly] Hull]]) 598 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinished 4th.\n\n===Guay, Raymond ([[Kamouraska\u2014Rivi\u00e8re-du-Loup]]) 349 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Lapierre, Andre Constance ([[Kamouraska\u2014Rivi\u00e8re-du-Loup]]) 358 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nThe combined vote of the two candidates was enough to rank 4th.\n\n===Collin, Gaston ([[Labelle_(electoral_district)|Labelle]]) 664 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Gagnon, Richard Amouthd ([[Labelle_(electoral_district)|Labelle]]) 331 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n\n===Morin, Jean-Marie ([[Labelle_(electoral_district)|Labelle]]) 580 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nThe combined vote of the three candidates was enough to rank 4th.\n\n===Briand, Beru Louis ([[Lac-Saint-Jean]]) 1,159 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\n===Baribeau, Jean Serge ([[Lachine (electoral district)|Lachine]]) 692 votes <ref name=\"EC\" />===\nFinishe